Here are some best practices to follow while working with Git.

1- Handle Merge Conflicts
	Use "git status" to identify the conflict
	Then manually resolve them in the IDE when merging test results or framework update

2- The use of ".gitignore"
	To ensure large that  test report folders, ".env" files which contains credentials, and "node_modules" are not pushed to the repository

3- Commit Often
	Always submit small, focused commits for better traceability

4- Link Tickets
	Alway specify the reference Jira or the issue ID in the commit messages
	e.g.: git commit -m "Fix login test - JIRA-405"

